'''Jørgen Strand Larsen''' ({{IPA|no|ˈjøːɾɡən strɑn ˈlɑːɾsən|lang}}, born 6 February 2000) is a Norwegian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[striker (association football)|striker]] for {{English football updater|CrystalP}} club [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] and the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]]. He is known for his link-up play, aerial ability and mobility.{{refn|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4052628|title=Why Strand Larsen is a perfect fit to lead Wolves' attack|work=[[Premier League]]|first=Adrian|last=Clarke|date=July 6, 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cjellpq8dvpo|title=The numbers behind Larsen's first year at Wolves|work=[[British Broadcasting Corporation|BBC.com]]|date=July 1, 2025|first=Tom|last=McCoy}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6035934/2025/01/06/wolves-jorgen-strand-larsen-analysis/|title=Jorgen Strand Larsen is already Wolves' best No 9 since Raul Jimenez – but there's room to improve|author=Steve Madeley, Thom Harris|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=January 6, 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fotmob.com/topnews/20568-jorgen-strand-larsen-no-9-wolves-have-been-waiting|title=Jorgen Strand Larsen: The No. 9 Wolves have been waiting for|work=Fotmob.com|date=April 15, 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://theanalyst.com/articles/jorgen-strand-larsen-wolves-impact-stats|title=Wolves' Fox in the Box: Jørgen Strand Larsen's Emergence Ends the Search for Raúl Jiménez's Heir|work=[[Opta Sports|Opta Analyst]]|date=April 26, 2025|first=Ryan|last=Benson}}</ref>}}

Strand Larsen began his senior career at [[Eliteserien]] side [[Sarpsborg 08 FF|Sarpsborg 08]] in 2017, and later went on to play for [[Eredivisie]] side [[FC Groningen|Groningen]], [[La Liga]] club [[RC Celta de Vigo|Celta de Vigo]], and Premier League side [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]]. In 2026, he was signed for a club-record fee of £48 million by Crystal Palace, winning the [[2025–26 UEFA Conference League|UEFA Conference League]] in his first season.

A former youth international, Strand Larsen made his senior debut for Norway in 2020, later helping them to qualification for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].

==Early life==
Jørgen Strand Larsen<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fotball.no/fotballdata/person/profil/?fiksId=3046363 |title=Jørgen Strand Larsen: Klubbstatistikk |trans-title=Jørgen Strand Larsen: Club statistics |publisher=Norwegian Football Federation |access-date=6 May 2023}}</ref> was born on 6 February 2000 in [[Halden]], [[Østfold]].<ref name="Soccerway">{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/jorgen-strand-larsen/461807/ |title=J. Strand Larsen: Summary |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=6 May 2023}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
[[File:Jørgen Strand Larsen 2019, Zen-Sarp (cropped).jpg|left|thumb|Strand Larsen with [[Sarpsborg 08 FF|Sarpsborg 08]] in 2019]]
Strand Larsen started his career as a youth player with [[Kvik Halden FK|Kvik Halden]] before joining [[Sarpsborg 08 FF|Sarpsborg 08]].<ref name=wolves>{{cite web |url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/teams/mens-first-team/jorgen-strand-larsen/ |title=Jorgen Strand Larsen |publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C. |access-date=4 September 2024 }}</ref> During this time he also played other sports, including tennis, ice hockey and golf.<ref>{{cite web |title= Strand Larsen, el fan del Liverpool y del pulpo que amenaza a España|url=https://www.relevo.com/futbol/eurocopa-masculina/strand-larsen-liverpool-pulpo-amenaza-20230322085751-nt.html|website=relevo |access-date=24 March 2023}}</ref> On 26 April, Strand Larsen made his debut with the senior team in a [[Norwegian Football Cup|cup match]], where he scored a hat trick in a 10–1 win against Drøbak-Frogn IL.<ref name=wolves /> Strand Larsen made his league debut on 21 May 2017 as a [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] against [[Vålerenga Fotball|Vålerenga]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2017/05/21/norway/eliteserien/fotballklubben-sparta-sarpsborg/valerengen-idrettsforeningen/2383923/ |title=Sarpsborg 08 vs. Valerenga  2 – 0 |publisher=Soccerway |access-date=4 September 2024 }}</ref> He was soon [[Loan (association football)|loaned out]] to the [[AC Milan Youth Sector|AC Milan Primavera]] and spent the entire 2017–18 season playing youth football in Italy. However, as Milan decided against the complete transfer, he returned to the club in July 2018.<ref>{{cite web |title=Jørgen Strand Larsen klar for AC Milan |url=https://www.sa.no/sport/sarpsborg-08/jorgen-strand-larsen/jorgen-strand-larsen-klar-for-ac-milan/s/5-46-389746|website=[[Stavanger Aftenblad]]|access-date=17 August 2018|language=no}}</ref>

On 9 September 2020, Strand Larsen signed a four-year contract with [[Eredivisie]] club [[FC Groningen|Groningen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-oranje.com/groningen-sign-norwegian-striker/|title=Groningen sign Norwegian striker|website=football-oranje.com|date=9 September 2020|access-date=2 June 2025}}</ref> He debuted as a starter in a 3–1 defeat to [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]], in which he contributed an assist.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://targetscouting.com/2020/09/16/fc-groningen-match-report-vs-psv-eindhoven-13-09-2020/|title=FC Groningen – Match Report vs PSV Eindhoven 13/09/2020|website=targetscouting.com|first=Josse|last=van Bakel|date=16 September 2020|access-date=2 June 2025}}</ref> Strand Larsen was selected in the Eredivisie Team of the Month for November 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Ajax Vierde Keer Hofleverancier in Eredivisie Elftsl van de Mand|url=https://eredivisie.nl/nieuws/ajax-vierde-keer-hofleverancier-in-eredivisie-elftal-van-de-maand/|website=Eredivisie|access-date=3 December 2021|language=nl}}</ref> He was named as Groningen's Player of the Year in May 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/strandlarsen/p/CdltezQoyP3/|title=Thanks for the player of the year, and thanks for your support this year!💚 Forza Groningen 💚|website=Instagram|first=Jørgen Strand|last=Larsen|date=15 May 2022|access-date=2 June 2025}}</ref>

===Celta===
Strand Larsen signed for [[La Liga]] club [[RC Celta de Vigo|Celta]] in August 2022 for a [[transfer fee]] of €11&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Coudet analiza el fichaje de Strand Larsen: "La incógnita, saber cuánto tiempo de aclimatación le va a llevar |url=https://www.eldesmarque.com/vigo/celta/noticias/177085-coudet-analiza-el-fichaje-de-strand-larsen-la-incognita-saber-cuanto-tiempo-de-aclimatacion-le-va-a-llevar|website=eldesmarque|access-date=1 September 2022|language=es}}</ref><ref name="Eurosport Norge 2022">{{Cite web|title=Jørgen Strand Larsen er Skuffet og Frustrert Over Groningen Etter Flere Blud: "Skulle Ønske de Kunne Ha Solgt Meg"|url=https://www.eurosport.no/fotball/skuffet-og-frustrert-over-egen-klubb-skulle-onske-de-kunne-ha-solgt-meg_sto9078301/story.shtml|website=eurosport.no|access-date=10 August 2022|language=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Stor Interesse Rundt Landslagsspiss {{!}} Kan Bli Solgt Allerede i Sommer|url=https://www.eurosport.no/fotball/stor-interesse-rundt-landslagsspiss-kan-bli-solgt-allerede-i-sommer_sto8999953/story.shtml|website=eurosport.no|access-date=20 June 2022|language=no}}</ref> On 2 September, he contributed an assist on his debut, a 3–0 win over [[Cádiz CF|Cádiz]] in La Liga.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-espana.net/2022/09/03/celta-vigo-cruise-to-3-0-cadiz-win|title=Celta Vigo cruise to 2–0 Cadiz win|website=football-espana.net|first=Feargal|last=Brennan|date=3 September 2022|access-date=2 June 2025}}</ref> He scored his first goal in the competition on 13 January 2023, in the 68th minute of a 1–1 draw against [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Larsen on his first goal for Celta: "I'm very happy, it's been a tough few months" |url=https://www.besoccer.com/new/larsen-on-his-first-goal-for-celta-i-m-very-happy-it-s-been-a-tough-few-months-1219598|website=BeSoccer|access-date=15 January 2023}}</ref> In the [[2023–24 La Liga|2023–24 season]], he was the top scorer for his club in La Liga with 13 goals.<ref>{{cite web |last=Sharma |first=Abhinav |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/la-liga-top-scorers-2023-24/bltc1315b7e4f725363#csea879fcd6919475e |title=La Liga top scorers 2023–24: Jude Bellingham, Robert Lewandowski & players with the most goals in Spain this season |publisher=Goal.com |date=27 May 2024 }}</ref> During his time at Celta, he was affectionately known as Xurxo, the [[Galician language|Galician]] form of his name.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elmundo.es/deportes/futbol/2024/03/10/65eb3ddffc6c83e62e8b457d.html|title="Xurxo" Strand Larsen, el otro gigante noruego: de una adolescencia con Haaland al pulpo y los goles en el Celta|work=[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]|date=10 March 2024|access-date=2 July 2024|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://rccelta.es/equipo/actualidad/jorgen-strand-larsen-emprende-una-nueva-etapa-deportiva-en-el-wolverhampton/|title=Jorgen Strand Larsen emprende una nueva etapa deportiva en el Wolverhampton|publisher=RC Celta de Vigo|date=2 July 2024 |access-date=2 July 2024|language=es}}</ref>

===Wolverhampton Wanderers===
[[File:Jørgen Strand Larsen 01112025 (6).jpg|thumb|left|200px|Strand Larsen during his time at Wolverhampton Wanderers.]]

On 2 July 2024, Strand Larsen signed for [[Premier League]] club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] on an initial loan deal with a €30&nbsp;million option to buy.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/mens-first-team/20240702-strand-larsen-completes-wolves-loan-move/|title=Strand Larsen completes Wolves loan move|date=2 July 2024 |access-date=2 July 2024 |publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.}}</ref> On 25 August, he scored his first goal for Wolves in a 6–2 loss to [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cgjvyxxqj11t|title=Wolverhampton Wanderers 2–6 Chelsea|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Timothy|last=Abraham|date=25 August 2024|access-date=2 June 2025}}</ref> Strand Larsen later began a scoring run in March 2025,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cwyjvl4ynkrt|title=Southampton 1–2 Wolverhampton Wanderers|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Matthew|last=Howarth|date=15 April 2025|access-date=2 June 2025}}</ref> and his form in April, which included netting in three consecutive matches,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c4g22lm0gevt|title=Wolverhampton Wanderers 4–2 Tottenham Hotspur|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Phil|last=McNulty|author-link=Phil McNulty|date=13 April 2025|access-date=2 June 2025}}</ref> saw him earn a nomination for [[Premier League Player of the Month|Player of the Month]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/4298451|title=April 2025 EA SPORTS Player of the Month shortlist|publisher=Premier League|date=1 May 2025|access-date=2 June 2025}}</ref> He finished his debut season with 14 goals, making him his club's second-highest scorer behind [[Matheus Cunha]].<ref>{{cite web |last=McCoy |first=Tom |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cjellpq8dvpo |title=The numbers behind Larsen's first year at Wolves |publisher=BBC Sport |date=1 July 2025 }}</ref>

On 1 July, Wolves announced that Strand Larsen had signed for the club permanently until 2029 after the option to buy in his loan deal was met.<ref>{{cite web|title=Strand Larsen becomes permanent Wolves player|url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/mens-first-team/20250701-strand-larsen-becomes-permanent-wolves-player/|publisher=[[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]]|date=1 July 2025|access-date=1 July 2025}}</ref> Over the summer, the club rejected two bids for Strand Larsen from [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]], the second believed to be worth £55 million.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Oakhill |first=Alex |date=2025-09-01 |title=Jorgen Strand Larsen to Newcastle takes twist after deal agreed |url=https://www.footballinsider247.com/jorgen-strand-larsen-to-newcastle-takes-twist-after-deal-agreed/ |access-date=2025-09-04 |website=Football Insider |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 19 September 2025, following the rejection of multiple transfer bids during the summer transfer window, Strand Larsen signed a new five-year contract with Wolves, with an option for an additional year.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mashiter |first=Nick |date=2025-09-19 |title=Wolves: Jorgen Strand Larsen agrees new five-year deal |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cgmz22wyz28o |access-date=2025-09-19 |publisher=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

===Crystal Palace===

On 2 February 2026, Strand Larsen was signed by fellow [[Premier League]] club [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] for a club-record fee worth up to £48 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-02-02 |title=Crystal Palace transfer news: Jorgen Strand Larsen arrives in club record deal worth up to £48m |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c62re2gdxqqo |access-date=2026-02-02 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 8 February, Strand Larsen made his debut for Palace, playing the full match in a 1–0 win at [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c0410xkr72wt|title=Premier League LIVE:Crystal Palace beat Brighton to end winless run|date=8 February 2026|access-date=15 February 2026|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> Three days later, he scored twice against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] on his home debut.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-02-12 |title=Strand Larsen's thoughts on home debut & brace against Burnley|url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/first-team/strand-larsen-on-his-home-debut-brace-against-burnley/ |access-date=2026-02-12 |website=CPFC|language=en-GB}}</ref> He scored his first European goal in the away leg of the semi-final game against [[Shakhtar Donetsk]] on 30 Apr 2026.<ref>{{Cite web |title='If Kane scored that we'd be saying wow' - Strand Larsen shows Palace worth |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/ce3pwqw02zjo |access-date=2026-05-01 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

==International career==
Strand Larsen played for the [[Norway national under-17 football team|Norway under-17 national team]] at the [[2017 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]], in which he scored a goal against [[Netherlands national under-17 football team|the Netherlands]] in a 2–2 draw in the group stage.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under17/match/2022599--netherlands-vs-norway/standings/|title=Netherlands 2–2 Norway|website=uefa.com|date=7 May 2017|access-date=2 June 2025}}</ref>

In November 2020, Strand Larsen received his first call-up to the [[Norway national football team|Norwegian senior team]],<ref>{{Cite web|title=Her er Norges tropp til Østerrike-kampen|url=https://www.fotball.no/landslag/norge-a-herrer/2020/her-er-norges-tropp-til-osterrike-kampen/|website=Norwegian Football Federation|access-date=16 November 2020}}</ref> debuting against [[Austria national football team|Austria]].<ref name="Eurosport Norge 2022"/> On 7 September 2023, Strand Larsen scored his first senior goal for Norway and contributed two assists in a 6–0 friendly win against [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]].<ref>{{Cite news|first1=Jostein|last1=Overvik|first2=Steffen|last2=Stenersen|first3=Bjørn S.|last3=Delebekk|title=VG-børsen: Haaland-erstatter Jørgen Strand Larsen herjet med Jordan|url=https://www.vg.no/sport/fotball/i/RGppra/haaland-erstatter-joergen-strand-larsen-herjet-med-jordan|website=[[Verdens Gang]]|date=7 September 2023|language=no}}</ref>

On 16 November 2025, he scored a stoppage-time goal in a 4–1 away victory over [[Italy national football team|Italy]] during the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]], inflicting the hosts' worst home defeat since 1983 and securing his nation's place at the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/mens-first-team/20251117-internationals-strand-larsen-scores-as-norway-reach-world-cup/ |title=Internationals {{!}} Strand Larsen scores as Norway reach World Cup |publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C. |date=17 November 2025 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.iffhs.com/posts/4751 |title=IFFHS WORLD STATS – WORLD CUP QUALIFIERS |publisher=IFFHS |date=17 November 2025 }}</ref>

